        private static int parseInt(String str) {
            int i, n = 0;

            for (i = 0; i &lt; str.length(); i++) {
                n *= 10;
                n += str.charAt(i) - 48;
            }

            return n;
        }
```

 2. For both positive and negative integers:

```java
        private static int parseInt(String str) {
            int i = 0, n = 0, sign = 1;
            if (str.charAt(0) == &#39;-&#39;) {
                i = 1;
                sign = -1;
            }

            for (; i &lt; str.length(); i++) {
                n *= 10;
                n += str.charAt(i) - 48;
            }

            return sign * n;
        }
```

 3. If you are expecting whitespace before or after these numbers,
